1
00:00:00,110 --> 00:00:05,720
In this video we are going to learn skills design pattern with event sourcing pattern.

2
00:00:06,320 --> 00:00:11,480
In the last video, we have learned the sequence pattern and the sequence pattern is mostly using with

3
00:00:11,480 --> 00:00:12,860
the event sourcing pattern.

4
00:00:13,340 --> 00:00:19,820
When using sequence with event sourcing pattern, the main idea is store events into right database

5
00:00:19,820 --> 00:00:24,260
and these will be the source of truth of that events database.

6
00:00:24,620 --> 00:00:30,830
After that, the right database of skills design pattern provides materialized views of the data with

7
00:00:30,830 --> 00:00:32,119
denormalized tables.

8
00:00:32,479 --> 00:00:39,020
Of course, these materialized views read databases, consume events from the right database and convert

9
00:00:39,020 --> 00:00:40,760
them into denormalized views.

10
00:00:41,660 --> 00:00:43,820
The writing database is never saved.

11
00:00:43,820 --> 00:00:44,900
Status of data.

12
00:00:44,900 --> 00:00:47,450
Only events actions are stored.

13
00:00:48,410 --> 00:00:52,550
By this way, saving only events actions into right database.

14
00:00:52,550 --> 00:00:59,000
We can store history of data and able to reply any point of time in order to regenerate the status of

15
00:00:59,000 --> 00:00:59,780
the data.

16
00:01:00,440 --> 00:01:06,170
So with following the event sourcing pattern, the system can increase the query performance and scale

17
00:01:06,170 --> 00:01:07,760
the databases independently.

18
00:01:09,500 --> 00:01:11,630
Here you can see the image on the slide.

19
00:01:11,630 --> 00:01:15,590
An example use case for applying queries and event sourcing pattern.

20
00:01:16,040 --> 00:01:21,800
Event sourcing pattern offers to save all events into database with sequential order of data events.

21
00:01:21,830 --> 00:01:24,470
This event database called Event Store.

22
00:01:24,470 --> 00:01:26,660
Here you can see the event store in here.

23
00:01:26,660 --> 00:01:30,860
In this architecture we are not updating the status of data record.

24
00:01:30,890 --> 00:01:35,450
It appends each change in a sequential list of the events.

25
00:01:35,450 --> 00:01:41,510
So that means these events store is become a source of truth for the data.

26
00:01:41,990 --> 00:01:47,990
After that these events store convert the data to the read database with following the materialized

27
00:01:47,990 --> 00:01:48,890
view patterns.

28
00:01:49,340 --> 00:01:56,570
This convert operations can handle by such publish subscribe pattern with publish event to the message

29
00:01:56,570 --> 00:01:59,600
broker system, and this will consume from the read database.

